### Why This Split?

| Concern | Handled By | Why? |
|---------|-----------|------|
| Auth, sessions, CRUD, real-time SSE | **Node.js (Express)** | Non-blocking I/O, excellent Clerk/Prisma/SSE ecosystem |
| Repo cloning, AST parsing, embeddings, LLM calls | **FastAPI (Python)** | Python dominates ML/NLP — sentence-transformers, Tree-sitter, LangChain all native |
| Evaluation (RAGAS) | **FastAPI (Python)** | RAGAS is a Python-only library |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Node.js gateway is the **single entry point** for the frontend. It proxies AI requests to FastAPI internally. This means the frontend never calls FastAPI directly — cleaner CORS, simpler auth, one deployment URL.

