## 3. The Free Stack — Every Component Justified

### 3.1 LLM Inference (replaces Claude API from your roadmap)

You have **two strategies** — use them together for resilience:

| Option | Model | Limits | Best For |
|--------|-------|--------|----------|
| **Groq API (Primary)** | Llama 3.3 70B / Llama 4 Maverick | 30 RPM, ~6K–30K TPM, 1000–14400 RPD, **no credit card** | Production queries — fast inference (~500 tok/s) |
| **Ollama (Fallback/Dev)** | Qwen 3.5 Coder / DeepSeek V3.2 / Llama 4 8B | Unlimited — runs on your machine | Local dev, fallback when Groq rate-limited, offline demos |

**Recommendation**: Use **Groq as primary** (it's blazing fast and free). Build an abstraction layer so you can swap between Groq and Ollama with a single environment variable. For your interview demo, run Ollama locally so you're never dependent on external APIs.

```python
# ai_service/llm_provider.py — Abstraction pattern
import os
from openai import OpenAI

def get_llm_client():
    provider = os.getenv("LLM_PROVIDER", "groq")  # or "ollama"
    if provider == "groq":
        return OpenAI(api_key=os.getenv("GROQ_API_KEY"), base_url="https://api.groq.com/openai/v1")
    else:
        return OpenAI(api_key="ollama", base_url="http://localhost:11434/v1")
```

### 3.2 Embeddings (replaces OpenAI text-embedding-3-small)

| Model | Dimensions | Size | Why |
|-------|-----------|------|-----|
| **`nomic-ai/nomic-embed-code-v1`** (Primary) | 768 | ~150MB | Purpose-built for **code retrieval** — understands syntax, function signatures |
| **`BAAI/bge-m3`** (Alternative) | 1024 | ~2GB | Best general-purpose model, supports hybrid search natively |
| **`BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5`** (Lightweight) | 384 | ~130MB | If your machine has limited RAM |

**Recommendation**: Start with **`nomic-embed-code-v1`** — it's specifically designed for code and lightweight enough to run on CPU. Run it via `sentence-transformers` in your FastAPI service.

```python
# ai_service/embedder.py
from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer

model = SentenceTransformer("nomic-ai/nomic-embed-code-v1")

def embed(texts: list[str]) -> list[list[float]]:
    return model.encode(texts, normalize_embeddings=True).tolist()
```

> [!TIP]
> You can also run embedding models via **Ollama** (`ollama pull nomic-embed-text`) for a unified local inference setup. This gives you a REST API at `http://localhost:11434/api/embeddings` without writing any Python embedding code.

