### 3.8 Deployment

| Component | Platform | Cost |
|-----------|----------|------|
| Frontend (Next.js) | **Vercel** | $0 (Hobby plan) |
| Node.js Gateway | **Render** Free Web Service | $0 (750 hrs/month, cold starts after 15m) |
| FastAPI AI Service | **Render** Free Web Service | $0 (same pool) |
| FastAPI Eval Service | **Render** Free Web Service | $0 (same pool) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Render gives you **750 free instance hours total** across all services. Running 3 services 24/7 = 2,160 hours — you'll exceed the limit. **Solution**: Merge the two FastAPI services into one, giving you 2 services × 750 hrs = enough for ~16 hrs/day uptime. For demos, wake them with a health-check cron.

### 3.9 AST Parsing — Tree-sitter

Use **`py-tree-sitter`** (Python bindings) in the FastAPI service. Supports Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, Go, Rust, C/C++.

Alternatively, for the Node.js gateway (if you want file-tree rendering), use **`web-tree-sitter`** (WASM-based, works in Node.js).

